President Biden and Speaker Pelosi had a phone conversation regarding the ongoing evacuation operations in Afghanistan, as well as the President's Build Back Better agenda. The President updated Speaker Pelosi on the progress made in evacuating American citizens, allies, and vulnerable Afghans. They also discussed the upcoming House action on key domestic issues. The President expressed his support for Speaker Pelosi's work on advancing the rule for the Bipartisan Infrastructure Bill and the Build Back Better Agenda. These initiatives aim to reduce prescription drug costs, housing and education expenses, strengthen care for veterans, address climate change, and make childcare and care for older Americans more affordable. The President and Speaker Pelosi also discussed the consensus reached with 15 House committee chairs on funding these long-term investments by allowing Medicare to negotiate lower prescription drug prices and ensuring that the largest corporations and wealthiest Americans pay their fair share.